  <tr align='left' valign='top' bgcolor='#E6E6E6'>
    <td><strong>Kuyana </strong>Wrote &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2000/12/20 15:25 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	<a href='modify.php3?table=top_general&id=2&modnum=96'>Mod</a>&nbsp;
	<hr noshade width='80%' align='left' color='#cccccc'><br>I made a judgement call that I think most of&nbsp;&nbsp;you guys thought was wrong.&nbsp;&nbsp;It was not cowardness that made me camp but a tactic that I have heard about.&nbsp;&nbsp;I don't know if it was right or wrong but I will post to as why I did this.<br>
<br>
As soon as Yilza was down I felt that we could not overcome the odds.&nbsp;&nbsp;Rather than have everyone die and have a long process of CR and rebuff while the tree gains more health, I decided to call camp.&nbsp;&nbsp;My idea was to have the party back up attacking the still wounded tree as quick as possible by saving the buffing/mana classes (cleric shaman and necros).<br>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;LoS (legacy of steel) has done this tactic with many of the uber mobs in SoV when it looks like you are not going to win.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since these new mobs have so many Hps you can usually re-engage when the mob is still substantially wounded because of the quickness of the sprinkler res.<br>
<br>
I really hope you don't think that I camped out because I did not want to die.&nbsp;&nbsp;I could have cared less to have died there because I know I will get a res and recover my corpse.&nbsp;&nbsp;Xp loss is laughing matter when you only loose 4%.<br>
<br>
Finally I have seen Fayl get down to the F in the health bar around three times now and we all died even with a good amount of people still in combat.&nbsp;&nbsp;Of course these were not ToP members also.<br>
<br>
If&nbsp;&nbsp;you think I was overriding Yilza's authority on what he wanted then I guess I did.&nbsp;&nbsp;I can do nothing but say I am sorry to everyone attending the raid for this.&nbsp;&nbsp;He was not there to see what was happening.&nbsp;&nbsp;So I decided to do something.&nbsp;&nbsp;If people have a problem with me doing this I won't do it again.&nbsp;&nbsp;Just please let me know.<BR><BR></td>
  </tr>
  
